cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with indoor radio propagation channels and device-free localization, which are relevant topics in the field of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses statistical and spatial models for the three states of the received signal strength, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a device-free localization application that involves tracking a person using a particle filter, which is a control system technique. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with radio propagation channels, which are relevant for wireless multimedia communication. 
5. cs.PE (Performance) - The paper proposes a simplistic device-free localization application that aims to enhance tracking accuracy and link sensitivity, which are performance metrics.
